content.rendered:
Isobiotics

Isobiotics features a user-friendly interface for viewing blood and food intolerance tests. Doctors have the ability to review results, write comments, and recommend supplements, while the company’s team manages the addition of vitamins and products. Future enhancements include integrating a nutritionist section and expanding the range of offerings.

About

Brand: Isobiotics

Location: Manchester, United Kingdom

Industry: Healthcare

Budget:: $10,000 to $49,999

Clutch Review: 

5.0
 5/5

Product link: isobiotics.com

Type of software: Web App

Scope of work: Back-end, Front-end, UI/UX Design, Project Management, Quality Assurance

Isobiotics is a user-friendly portal that enables customers to access and view their test results. The portal accommodates both blood and food intolerance tests, displaying results in an intuitive format.

Doctors have access to review results, write comments, and recommend supplements, facilitating effective collaboration with customers.

Technologies

PHP

Laravel

Docker

MySQL

API Platform

Shopify API Library for PHP

Vue.js

NGINX

What our client
wanted

Aaron Ware

Founder, Isobiotics

We needed to create a Web Portal for blood and food intolerance test results with capability to provide personalized recommendations for each client

Challenge

  • The main challenge was to enhance the customer experience by providing a centralized platform for accessing test results and receiving personalized recommendations

Key Functional features​

  • Registration and login
  • Home page with available test results;
  • Redirect to buy tests and/or supplements;
  • Detailed page of the food intolerance tests;
  • Detailed page of the blood tests, biomarkers details;
  • Home page with pending tests to complete the review;
  • Ability to create a review and suggest supplements on blood tests;
  • Ability to suggest supplements on food intolerance tests.

Project Team

Diana

Project Manager​

Vasyl

Tech Lead developer

Dmytro

Back-end Developer

Oksana

UX/UI Designer

Dima

Frontend developer

QA Engineer

Client’s review

Aaron Ware

Founder at Isobiotics

Their attention to detail in ensuring data security and compliance with healthcare regulations was impressive, and it instilled confidence in both me and my users. I appreciated their responsiveness to my questions and concerns, which made the development process smooth and efficient

5.0
 5/5

Business Value

We made the application clear and accessible for different types of target audiences

We connected clients, partners and doctors, which made it possible to solve user problems based on both food intolerance test results and blood test results.

We created an intuitive UI/UX, which, among other things, will significantly improve the customer experience

Let's start. It's easier than you think.
